\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. N. rustica} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 180 (1753). Annual; stem 0·5-1·5 m, viscid-pubescent. Leaves 10-15(-30) cm, ovate to elliptical or rarely suborbicular, acute, puberulent; petiole not winged. Flowers numerous in a compact to lax panicle. Calyx 8-15 mm, tubular to cupuliform; teeth triangular, acute, unequal. Corolla 12-17 mm, tubular-infundibuliform, greenish-yellow; limb 3-6 mm, with short, obtuse, apiculate lobes. Stamens unequal, inserted in basal ¼ of corolla-tube. Capsule 7-16 mm, ellipsoid-ovoid to subglobose.{\i  Formerly widely cultivated for tobacco and locally naturalized; now largely replaced by }{\b 3}. [Al Au Be ?Bl Bu Co ?Cr Cz ?Da Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) ?Sa ?Si ?Tu.] ({\i North America}.)
